Class ComException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • com4j.ComException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public class ComException
extends RuntimeException
    Signals a failure in the COM method invocation.

    Calling a wrapped COM method throws this exception when the underlying COM method returns a failure HRESULT code.

    Author:
    Kohsuke Kawaguchi (kk@kohsuke.org)
    See Also:

      • getErrorInfo

        public ErrorInfo getErrorInfo()
        Gets the ErrorInfo object associated with this error.

        Some COM objects can report additional error information beyond simple HRESULT value. If an error came from such an COM object, this method returns a non-null value, and you can query the returned ErrorInfo object for more information about the error.

        Returns:
        null if this exception doesn't have such detailed information.
